H0175.meaning: Hebrew אַהֲרוֹן (Aharon); etymology uncertain—possibly Egyptian, or from Hebrew 'mountaineer' or 'enlightened.' Not from a common Hebrew root; name predates Exodus. Hitchcock: a teacher; lofty; mountain of strength. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אַהֲרֹן (ʾAharon), most likely of unknown Egyptian origin. Other theories suggest 'high mountain' or 'exalted'.
H0175.significance: First high priest; establishes the Aaronic priesthood. Type of Christ as priest (Heb 5–7): offers sacrifice, mediates, bears the people’s names. His rod buds (Num 17)—life from death; his line endures.

H0005.meaning: Persian name; not Hebrew. Likely related to Persian baga (god) + a theophoric element. One of seven eunuchs of Ahasuerus (Xerxes). Hitchcock: father of the wine-press
H0005.significance: Minor court official; represents the Gentile royal household in Esther. Eunuchs often gatekeepers of access to the king—ironic backdrop to Esther’s risk to approach.

H5653.meaning: From עָבַד (avad), to serve, work. Abda = servant. Father of Adoram (1 Ki 4:6), who was over forced labor. Hitchcock: a servant; servitude
H5653.significance: His name (servant) fits his son’s role: Adoram oversaw the corvée. The house of “servant” administers forced service—naming echoes function in the monarchy.

H5655.meaning: From עָבַד (avad), serve, + אֵל (el), God. Abdeel = servant of God. Hitchcock: a vapor; a cloud of God
H5655.significance: Father of Shelemiah (Jer 36:26); named in the context of Baruch’s scroll and the king’s rejection. “Servant of God” in a line that confronts the king.

H5660.meaning: From עָבַד (avad); Abdi = my servant. Levite, time of Hezekiah (2 Chr 29:12).
H5660.significance: Levite in temple restoration under Hezekiah. Name (servant) fits cultic service; part of the cohort that cleanses and consecrates the house.

H5661.meaning: From עֶבֶד (eved), servant, + אֵל (el), God. Abdiel = servant of God. BehindTheName: Means 'servant of God' in Hebrew, from עֶבֶד (ʿeveḏ) 'servant' and אֵל (ʾel) 'God'.
H5661.significance: Son of Guni, Gadite (1 Chr 5:15). In a genealogy of the Transjordan tribes; “servant of God” in a line that will face exile (1 Chr 5:26).

H5658.meaning: From עָבַד (avad); Abdon = servitude. Judge in Israel (Judg 12:13–15); had 40 sons, 30 grandsons—symbol of lineage and donkeys (status). Hitchcock: servant; cloud of judgment
H5658.significance: Minor judge; name suggests servitude—perhaps to God or to the people. His many sons and donkeys imply wealth; judgeship as service, not dynasty.

H1893.meaning: Hebrew הֶבֶל (hevel), breath, vapor, vanity. Same word as in Ecclesiastes—transitory, fleeting. Second son of Adam. Hitchcock: vanity; breath; vapor | a city; mourning. BehindTheName: From Hebrew הֶבֶל (Hevel) meaning 'breath'.
H1893.significance: First righteous sacrifice (Gen 4:4); first murder victim. Type of Christ: acceptable offering, innocent blood, “speaks” after death (Heb 11:4). Name (breath) echoes life cut short.

H0021.meaning: From אָב (av), father; Abi = my father, or fatherly. Short form; Hezekiah’s mother (2 Ki 18:2), daughter of Zechariah.
H0021.significance: Mother of a reforming king; Hezekiah’s devotion may reflect her influence. Name (fatherly) could point to lineage or character.

H0029.meaning: From אָב (av) + יָהּ (Yah). Abijah = father (worshipper) of Yah. Multiple bearers: king of Judah (1 Ki 14:31), priest, others. Hitchcock: the Lord is my father. BehindTheName: Means 'my father is Yahweh' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and יָהּ (yah) referring to God.
H0029.significance: Abijah king: walked in his father Rehoboam’s sins (1 Ki 14:22–24). Name confesses Yah, but life did not—name vs. deed tension.

H0045.meaning: From אָב + strength (חַיִל or similar). Abi-albon = father of strength / valiant. One of David’s thirty (2 Sam 23:31). Hitchcock: most intelligent father
H0045.significance: Elite warrior under David; name (valiant) fits the Mighty Men. Part of the human “strength” that secures the kingdom.

H0054.meaning: From אָב + יָתַר (yatar), abundance, remainder. Abiathar = father of abundance. Priest, house of Eli. Hitchcock: excellent father; father of the remnant
H0054.significance: Priest who fled Saul with the ephod; supported David, then backed Adonijah. Solomon removed him—fulfillment of word against Eli’s house (1 Ki 2:27). Name (abundance) contrasts with his line’s end.

H0028.meaning: From אָב + יָדַע (yada), know. Abida = father of knowledge. Son of Abraham by Keturah (Gen 25:4).
H0028.significance: Son of the covenant patriarch by a secondary wife; sent east (Gen 25:6). Name (knowledge) in a line outside the main promise—knowledge of God vs. separation.

H0027.meaning: From אָב + דִּין (din), judgment. Abidan = father of judgment. Prince of Benjamin at the census (Num 1:11, 2:22).
H0027.significance: Tribal representative in the wilderness; name (judgment) fits the judicial role of princes. Part of the ordered camp around the tabernacle.

H0022.meaning: From אָב + אֵל (el), God. Abiel = father (possessor) of God, or God is father. Grandfather of Saul (1 Sam 9:1). Hitchcock: God my father
H0022.significance: Ancestor of Israel’s first king; name (God is father) contrasts with Saul’s later rejection. Line that began with a Godward name ends in loss of kingdom.

H0044.meaning: From אָב + עֵזֶר (ezer), help. Abiezer = father of help. Manassehite; Gideon’s clan (Judg 6:11, 34).
H0044.significance: Gideon’s clan—the “least” in Manasseh (Judg 6:15). Name (father of help) fits God’s pattern: help from the weak. First of the muster (Num 26:30).

H0026.meaning: From אָב + גִּיל (gil), joy. Abigail = father (source) of joy. Wife of Nabal, then David (1 Sam 25). Hitchcock: the father's joy. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אֲבִיגָיִל (ʾAviḡayil) meaning 'my father is joy', from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and גִּיל (gil) 'joy'.
H0026.significance: Wise woman who prevents David from bloodguilt; “source of joy” to David. Type of the wise bride who restrains and counsels; mother of Chileab.

H0032.meaning: From אָב + חַיִל (chayil), might, valor. Abihail = father of might. Multiple bearers (male and female). Hitchcock: the father of strength. BehindTheName: Means 'my father is strength' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and חַיִל (ḥayil) 'strength'.
H0032.significance: One Abihail is mother of Esther (Est 2:15)—“father of might” for the woman who risks all before the king. Name and role align.

H0030.meaning: From אָב + הוּא (hu), he/him. Abihu = father (worshipper) of Him (God). Son of Aaron (Ex 6:23). Hitchcock: he is my father. BehindTheName: Means 'he is my father' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and הוּא (hu) 'he'.
H0030.significance: Priest who offered strange fire (Lev 10:1–2) and died. Name (worshipper of Him) vs. act—worship on man’s terms. Warning against unauthorized approach.

H0031.meaning: From אָב + הוֹד (hod), splendor, majesty. Abihud = father of splendor. In Saul’s genealogy (1 Chr 8:3). Hitchcock: father of praise; confession
H0031.significance: Benjaminite in the line of Saul; name (splendor) in a house that lost the kingdom. Ironic given Saul’s fall.

H0040.meaning: From אָב + מֶלֶךְ (melek), king. Abimelech = my father is king. Title or name of several Philistine/Gerar kings (Gen 20, 26; Judg 9). Hitchcock: father of the king. BehindTheName: Means 'my father is king' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and מֶלֶךְ (meleḵ) 'king'.
H0040.significance: Gideon’s son Abimelech (Judg 9) claims kingship by blood and kills brothers—name (father is king) becomes usurpation. Shechem’s folly and his end at Thebez.

H0041.meaning: From אָב + נָדָב (nadav), willing, generous. Abinadab = father of willingness. Saul’s son (1 Sam 31:2); also the man in whose house the ark rested (1 Sam 7:1). Hitchcock: father of a vow, or of willingness
H0041.significance: Saul’s son died with him at Gilboa. Another Abinadab (Kiriath-jearim) housed the ark—same name, different fates: one death in battle, one honor of holding the ark.

H0042.meaning: From אָב + נֹעַם (noam), pleasantness. Abinoam = father of pleasantness. Father of Barak (Judg 4:6). Hitchcock: father of beauty
H0042.significance: Father of the military leader Barak; “pleasantness” in a time of oppression. Name suggests favor—Barak’s victory is the Lord’s pleasant work.

H0048.meaning: From אָב + רָם (ram), high, exalted. Abiram = my father is exalted. Reubenite; with Dathan and Korah (Num 16). Hitchcock: high father; father of deceit. BehindTheName: Means 'my father is exalted' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and רוּם (rum) 'to exalt'.
H0048.significance: Rebel against Moses and Aaron; earth swallows them (Num 16:32). Name (exalted father) vs. end—exaltation of self, not God. Type of presumption.

H0049.meaning: From אָב + שָׁגַג (shagag), err, stray. Abishag = father of error/wandering, or (alternately) source of ignorance. Young Shunammite who attended David (1 Ki 1:3–4). Hitchcock: ignorance of the father. BehindTheName: Means 'my father strays' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and שָׁגָה (shaḡa) 'to stray'.
H0049.significance: David’s attendant in old age; Adonijah’s request for her becomes his death sentence (1 Ki 2:17–25). She is the occasion of Solomon’s purge—innocent figure at the center of succession conflict.

H0052.meaning: From אָב + שַׁי (shay), gift, or from a root for present. Abishai = father of gift. Son of Zeruiah; David’s nephew, one of the three (2 Sam 23:18). Hitchcock: the present of my father. BehindTheName: Means 'my father is a gift' in Hebrew, from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and שַׁי (shai) 'gift'.
H0052.significance: Fierce warrior; often with David in crisis (e.g. 1 Sam 26:6–12). Wanted to strike Shimei (2 Sam 16:9)—loyalty and zeal, but David restrains. Name (gift) as the gift of fierce loyalty.

H0085.meaning: From אָב (av) + הָמוֹן (hamon), multitude. Abraham = father of a multitude (Gen 17:5); earlier Abram = exalted father. Hitchcock: father of a great multitude. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אַבְרָהָם (ʾAvraham), meaning 'father of many' or contraction of Abram and הָמוֹן (hamon) 'multitude'.
H0085.significance: Covenant patriarch; father of the faithful (Rom 4). Name change marks covenant: from exalted father to father of many nations. Type of faith and of the promised seed (Gal 3:16).

H053.meaning: From אָב + שָׁלוֹם (shalom), peace. Absalom = father of peace. David’s son (2 Sam 3:3).
H053.significance: Name (peace) vs. life: rebellion, war, death in a tree (2 Sam 18:9). Beautiful son who brings strife—ironic naming; type of the false peacemaker.

H5912.meaning: From עָכַר (akar), trouble. Achan = troubler. Took devoted things at Jericho (Josh 7). Hitchcock: or Achar, he that troubleth. BehindTheName: Possibly from Hebrew עֲכָר (ʿaḵar) meaning 'trouble'.
H5912.significance: One man’s sin brought defeat at Ai; “troubler of Israel” (Josh 7:25). Name and deed identical—his name is his crime. Type of corporate consequence of hidden sin.

H0121.meaning: Hebrew אָדָם (adam); from אֲדָמָה (adamah), ground. Adam = man, from the dust (Gen 2:7). Hitchcock: earthy; red. BehindTheName: Hebrew word for 'man', possibly from אדם (ʾaḏam) 'to be red' (ruddy skin) or Akkadian adamu 'to make'.
H0121.significance: First man; federal head of humanity. Type of Christ as head (Rom 5; 1 Cor 15:45–49): first Adam brought death, last Adam life. Name ties humanity to the ground and to the promise.

H0256.meaning: From אָח (ach), brother, + אָב (av), father. Ahab = brother (or uncle) of father. King of Israel (1 Ki 16:29). Hitchcock: uncle, or father's brother. BehindTheName: Means 'uncle' in Hebrew, from אָח (ʾaḥ) 'brother' and אָב (ʾav) 'father'.
H0256.significance: Did more evil than all before him (1 Ki 16:30); married Jezebel, served Baal. Elijah’s antagonist. Name (father’s brother) in a dynasty that broke the brotherhood of Israel.

H0325.meaning: Hebrew form of Old Persian Khshayarsha (Xerxes). Ahasuerus = ruler. Emperor in Esther (Est 1:1). Hitchcock: prince; head; chief. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אֲחַשְׁוֵרוֹשׁ, from Old Persian Xšayarša (Xerxes).
H0325.significance: King who does not know the true King; his decrees threaten the Jews, but the story turns on providence and Esther. Type of the Gentile ruler used for God’s people’s deliverance.

H0090.meaning: From אֲגָג (Agag); Amalekite king (1 Sam 15). Name may mean “flame” or be a title. Hitchcock: roof; upper floor
H0090.significance: Saul spared him against the ban (1 Sam 15:9); Samuel killed him (1 Sam 15:33). Type of incomplete obedience—Saul’s mercy becomes his downfall. Amalek = enemy of the throne (Ex 17:16).

H0316.meaning: From אָח (ach), brother, + הָר (har), mountain, or from a root for following. Aharhel = brother of the mountain. In Judah’s genealogy (1 Chr 4:8). Hitchcock: another host; the last sorrow; a brother's sheep
H0316.significance: Minor genealogical figure; name may point to kinship or place. In the line of Judah, the royal tribe.

H0271.meaning: From אָחַז (achaz), grasp, possess. Ahaz = he has grasped. King of Judah (2 Ki 16); made an altar like Damascus’s. Hitchcock: one that takes or possesses
H0271.significance: Did not do right (2 Ki 16:2); closed the house, sought Assyria. Isaiah’s sign of Immanuel is in his reign (Isa 7). Name (grasp) as grasping the wrong help.

H0274.meaning: From אָחַז + יָהּ. Ahaziah = Yah has grasped. Two kings: Israel (1 Ki 22:51) and Judah (2 Ki 8:25). Hitchcock: seizure; vision of the Lord
H0274.significance: Ahaziah of Israel walked in Ahab’s ways; died from fall, consulted Baal-zebub (2 Ki 1). Ahaziah of Judah walked in Ahab’s house (2 Ki 8:27). Both names confess Yah, both lives contradict.

H0138.meaning: From אָדוֹן (adon), lord, + יָהּ. Adonijah = my lord is Yah. Fourth son of David (2 Sam 3:4). Hitchcock: the Lord is my master. BehindTheName: Means 'my lord is Yahweh' in Hebrew, from אָדוֹן (ʾaḏon) 'lord' and יָהּ (yah) referring to God.
H0138.significance: Sought the kingdom while David lived (1 Ki 1:5); later requested Abishag and was put to death (1 Ki 2:25). Name (Yah is lord) vs. acting as his own lord.

H0137.meaning: From אָדוֹן + בֶּזֶק (bezeq), lightning or scatter. Adoni-bezek = lord of Bezek. Canaanite king (Judg 1:5–7). Hitchcock: the lightning of the Lord; the Lord of lightning
H0137.significance: Had cut off thumbs and big toes of 70 kings; same done to him—“as I did, so God has repaid me” (Judg 1:7). Type of lex talionis and of Gentile acknowledgment of divine justice.

H0139.meaning: From אָדוֹן + צֶדֶק (tzedek), righteousness. Adoni-zedek = lord of righteousness. King of Jerusalem (Josh 10:1). Hitchcock: justice of the Lord; lord of justice
H0139.significance: Led coalition against Gibeon; sun and moon “stand” at Joshua’s word (Josh 10:12–14). Canaanite “lord of righteousness” defeated by the true King’s captain.

H0152.meaning: From אָדְרַמֶּלֶךְ (Adrammelek); possibly “Adad is king” (Assyrian theophoric). Son of Sennacherib (2 Ki 19:37). Hitchcock: the cloak, glory, grandeur or power of the king
H0152.significance: With Sharezer, killed Sennacherib in the temple of Nisroch. Patricide after Assyria’s defeat; idol temple as scene of murder—fitting end for the house that defied the living God.

G0132.meaning: Greek Αἰνέας (Aineas); from Greek αἰνέω (praise). Aeneas = praised. Paralytic at Lydda (Acts 9:33–34). Hitchcock: praised; praiseworthy
G0132.significance: Healed by Peter—“Jesus Christ heals you.” Name (praised) fits the response: Lydda and Sharon turned to the Lord (Acts 9:35).

G0013.meaning: From Hebrew or Aramaic; possibly “locust” or “loved.” Agabus = prophet from Jerusalem (Acts 11:28, 21:10). Hitchcock: a locust; the father's joy or feast. BehindTheName: Greek form of Hagab.
G0013.significance: Prophesied famine (Acts 11:28) and Paul’s binding (Acts 21:10–11). Name less significant than function: prophet who speaks the Lord’s word to the church.

G0067.meaning: Greek Ἀγρίππας (Agrippas); Latin Agrippa, from “born with difficulty.” Herod Agrippa II (Acts 25–26). Hitchcock: one who causes great pain at his birth
G0067.significance: Hears Paul’s defense; “almost persuaded” (Acts 26:28). Judge who recognizes Paul’s innocence but does not free him. Name (difficult birth) and his dynasty’s troubled relation to the truth.

H0397.meaning: Philistine name; possibly “angry” or “only.” Achish = king of Gath (1 Sam 21, 27–29). Hitchcock: thus it is; how is this
H0397.significance: David’s refuge when fleeing Saul; feigned madness before him. Achish trusted David; Philistine lords did not (1 Sam 29). Gentile king who unwittingly shelters the anointed.

H5711.meaning: From עָדָה (adah), adorn, pass. Adah = ornament. Wife of Lamech (Gen 4:19–20), mother of Jabal and Jubal. Hitchcock: an assembly. BehindTheName: Means 'adornment, ornament' in Hebrew.
H5711.significance: In the line of Cain; her sons found tent-dwelling and music (Gen 4:20–21). “Ornament” in a cursed line—culture and creativity apart from the covenant.

H6002.meaning: From עֲמָלֵק (Amalek); possibly “people that lick” or “dweller in the valley.” Grandson of Esau (Gen 36:12). Hitchcock: a people that licks up
H6002.significance: Amalek attacks Israel at Rephidim (Ex 17:8); “war of YHWH against Amalek from generation to generation” (Ex 17:16). Type of persistent enemy of the throne; Agag (1 Sam 15) is his king.

H6021.meaning: From עָמַס (amas), load, carry. Amasa = burden. Nephew of David; Absalom’s general, then David’s (2 Sam 17:25, 19:13). Hitchcock: sparing the people
H6021.significance: Joab killed him (2 Sam 20:9–10)—rival to Joab. Name (burden) fits his role as commander and his death: he becomes a “burden” removed in the consolidation of power.

H0568.meaning: From אָמַר (amar), say, + יָהּ. Amariah = Yah has said. Multiple priests and Levites. Hitchcock: the Lord says; the integrity of the Lord. BehindTheName: Means 'Yahweh has said' in Hebrew, from אָמַר (ʾamar) 'to say' and יָהּ (yah) referring to God.
H0568.significance: Priests named Amariah serve in reform (2 Chr 19:11, 31:15). Name (Yah has said) fits the word-bound office—they teach and judge by the law.

G0223.meaning: Greek Ἀλέξανδρος (Alexandros); from ἀλέξω (ward off) + ἀνήρ (man). Alexander = defender of men. Several in NT. Hitchcock: one who assists men. BehindTheName: From Greek Ἀλέξανδρος (Alexandros) meaning 'defending men', from ἀλέξω (alexo) 'to defend' and ἀνήρ (aner) 'man'.
G0223.significance: One Alexander is a coppersmith who did Paul harm (2 Tim 4:14). Another in Acts 19:33 is pushed forward by Jews. Name (defender) vs. opposition to the gospel.

G0256.meaning: Greek Ἀλφαῖος (Alphaios); from Hebrew or Aramaic. Alphaeus = father of James (one of the Twelve) and possibly of Matthew/Levi. BehindTheName: Greek form of a Hebrew name meaning 'exchange'.
G0256.significance: Father of James the son of Alphaeus (Mk 3:18); if same as Clopas, then husband of Mary at the cross (Jn 19:25). Name links to the circle of Jesus’ family and disciples.

H0486.meaning: From אַלְמוֹדָד (Almodad); possibly “measure” or “God is friend.” Son of Joktan (Gen 10:26). Hitchcock: measure of God
H0486.significance: In the Table of Nations (Gen 10); Joktanite line in Arabia. Name in the genealogy that spreads after Babel—peoples and names without covenant.

H0011.meaning: Hebrew אֲבַדּוֹן (avaddon); from אָבַד (avad), perish. Abaddon = destruction, perishing; in Rev 9:11 the angel of the abyss. Hitchcock: the destroyer. BehindTheName: Means 'ruin, destruction' in Hebrew.
H0011.significance: Place or personification of destruction (Job 26:6; Rev 9:11). Name (perishing) as the realm or agent of ruin; contrast with the Lord who delivers from the pit.

H0024.meaning: Hebrew אָבִיב (aviv); from root meaning tender. Abib = green ear of grain; name of the first month (Ex 13:4). Hitchcock: green fruit; ears of corn
H0024.significance: Month of Passover and Exodus; name (green ear) marks new life and deliverance. Calendar name that ties redemption to the land.

H0074.meaning: From אָב (av) + נִיר (nir), light. Abner = father of light. Saul's cousin and army commander (1 Sam 14:50). BehindTheName: From Hebrew אַבְנֵר (ʾAvner) meaning 'my father is a light', from אָב (ʾav) 'father' and נֵר (ner) 'lamp, light'.
H0074.significance: Saul's general; after Saul's death supported Ish-bosheth, then defected to David. Joab killed him (2 Sam 3:27). Name (father of light) in a house that lost the kingdom.

H0078.meaning: From בָּצַן (batsan) or similar; Ibzan = judge. Judge of Israel (Judg 12:8–10); had 30 sons, 30 daughters. Hitchcock: father of a target; father of coldness
H0078.significance: Minor judge; gave his daughters in marriage outside his clan. Name in the line of judges between Jephthah and Elon.

H0164.meaning: From אֶחָד (echad), one; Ehud = united. Left-handed judge (Judg 3:15). Hitchcock: he that praises
H0164.significance: Judge who delivered Israel from Moab by killing Eglon (Judg 3:21). Left-handedness as unexpected weapon; name (united) as the one who unites Israel against the oppressor.

H0170.meaning: From אֹהֶל (ohel), tent. Oholah = her tent. Ezekiel's name for Samaria (Ezek 23:4).
H0170.significance: Elder sister in the allegory of the two adulterous sisters (Ezek 23); Samaria. Name (her tent) as Israel's dwelling corrupted by idolatry.

H0171.meaning: From אֹהֶל (ohel) + אָב (av). Oholiab = father's tent. Son of Ahisamach; craftsman for the tabernacle (Ex 31:6).
H0171.significance: Bezalel's partner in building the tabernacle; name (father's tent) fits the one who builds the dwelling of God.

H0172.meaning: From אֹהֶל (ohel). Oholibah = my tent is in her. Ezekiel's name for Jerusalem (Ezek 23:4).
H0172.significance: Younger sister in Ezek 23; Jerusalem. Name (my tent in her) as the city where God's tent dwells—yet she played the harlot.

H0192.meaning: Akkadian Amel-Marduk; Evil-merodach = man of Marduk. Babylonian king (2 Ki 25:27); son of Nebuchadnezzar. Hitchcock: the fool of Merodach; the fool grinds bitterly
H0192.significance: Released Jehoiachin from prison (2 Ki 25:27–30). Gentile king who shows kindness to the Davidic prisoner; unwittingly preserves the line.

H0209.meaning: From אוֹן (on), strength. Onan = vigor. Son of Judah (Gen 38:4).
H0209.significance: Refused to raise seed for his brother (Gen 38:9); God struck him down. Name (strength) vs. act—withheld strength; type of the one who refuses the duty of the kinsman.

H0223.meaning: From אוּר (ur) + יָהּ (yah). Uriah = my light is Yah. Hittite; husband of Bathsheba (2 Sam 11:3). Hitchcock: or Urijah, the Lord is my light or fire. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אוּרִיָה meaning 'Yahweh is my light'.
H0223.significance: Faithful soldier; David had him killed to take Bathsheba (2 Sam 11). Name (Yah is my light) vs. death in darkness—innocent blood; type of the faithful one betrayed by the king.

H0285.meaning: From אָח (ach) + טוּב (tuv), good. Ahitub = brother of goodness. High priest; father of Ahimelech (1 Sam 14:3).
H0285.significance: Priestly line of Eli; grandfather of Abiathar. Name (brother of goodness) in a house that will be cut off (1 Sam 2:31).

H0288.meaning: From אָח (ach) + מֶלֶךְ (melek). Ahimelech = brother of the king. Priest at Nob (1 Sam 21:1). Hitchcock: my brother is a king; my king's brother
H0288.significance: Gave David showbread and Goliath's sword; Saul had him and the priests of Nob killed (1 Sam 22). Name (brother of the king) as the priest who served the anointed—and paid with his life.

H0302.meaning: From אָח (ach) + תֹּפֶל (tophel), folly. Ahithophel = brother of folly. David's counselor (2 Sam 15:12). Hitchcock: brother of ruin or folly
H0302.significance: Counselor who joined Absalom's rebellion; his advice was like the word of God (2 Sam 16:23). When rejected he hanged himself (2 Sam 17:23). Name (brother of folly) as wisdom turned to folly—type of the counselor who betrays.

H3068.meaning: From הָיָה (hayah), to be. YHWH = He is / I AM (Ex 3:14). The tetragrammaton; covenant name of God.
H3068.significance: The name God gives Israel; the name by which he is known in covenant. I AM WHO I AM—being, presence, faithfulness. Name above every name until the Son bears it (Phil 2:9–11).

H4872.meaning: Hebrew מֹשֶׁה (Moshe); Egyptian element—“drawn out” (Ex 2:10). Possibly also Hebrew מָשָׁה (mashah), draw out. Hitchcock: taken out; drawn forth. BehindTheName: From Hebrew מֹשֶׁה (Moshe), possibly Egyptian in origin, traditionally 'drawn out' (Ex 2:10).
H4872.significance: Deliverer and lawgiver; type of Christ as prophet (Deut 18:15) and mediator. Drawn out of the water—Israel drawn out of Egypt. His face shone (Ex 34:29); the law’s glory points to the greater Prophet.

H3478.meaning: From שָׂרָה (sarah), strive, + אֵל (el), God. Israel = he strives with God (Gen 32:28). New name for Jacob after wrestling at Peniel. Hitchcock: who prevails with God. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יִשְׂרָאֵל possibly meaning 'God contends' or 'he who strives with God'.
H3478.significance: Covenant name of the people; prince with God. The one who strove and prevailed becomes the nation that bears the promise. Type of the church as the true Israel (Rom 9:6).

H3290.meaning: From עָקַב (aqav), heel, take by the heel. Jacob = supplanter. Son of Isaac; twin of Esau (Gen 25:26).
H3290.significance: Grasped Esau’s heel; later wrestles God and becomes Israel (Gen 32:28). Father of the twelve tribes. Type of the chosen line—grace over merit; the younger receives the blessing.

H3327.meaning: From צָחַק (tsachaq), laugh. Isaac = he laughs (Gen 21:3, 6). Son of Abraham and Sarah. Hitchcock: laughter. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יִצְחָק (Yiṣḥaq) meaning 'he will laugh', from צָחַק (ṣaḥaq) 'to laugh'.
H3327.significance: Son of promise; type of Christ as the offered son (Gen 22; Heb 11:17–19). Laughter of disbelief (Sarah) becomes laughter of joy. The seed through whom the covenant runs.

H1732.meaning: From דּוֹד (dod), beloved, or root דָּוִד (David). David = beloved. Second king of Israel (1 Sam 16:13). Hitchcock: well-beloved, dear. BehindTheName: From Hebrew דָּוִד (Dawiḏ), from דּוֹד (doḏ) 'beloved' or 'uncle'.
H1732.significance: King after God’s heart (1 Sam 13:14); type of Christ as king (2 Sam 7; Luke 1:32). Shepherd, psalmist, covenant recipient. His line endures forever.

H8010.meaning: From שָׁלוֹם (shalom), peace. Solomon = peaceable. Son of David; king of Israel (1 Ki 1:39). Hitchcock: peaceable; perfect; one who recompenses. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שְׁלֹמֹה (Shelomo) meaning 'peace', from שָׁלוֹם (shalom).
H8010.significance: Builder of the temple; wisdom and peace (1 Ki 4:24–25). Type of the peaceful reign; his fall (1 Ki 11) shows the need for a greater Son of David.

H3091.meaning: From יְהוֹשֻׁעַ (Yehoshua); יָהּ (Yah) + יָשַׁע (yasha), save. Joshua = YHWH saves. Successor of Moses (Num 27:18). Hitchcock: a savior; a deliverer. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יְהוֹשֻׁעַ (Yehoshuaʿ) meaning 'Yahweh is salvation'.
H3091.significance: Leads Israel into the land; type of Christ as captain of salvation (Heb 2:10). Same name as Jesus (Greek form). The Lord saves—in conquest and in gospel.

H4442.meaning: From מֶלֶךְ (melek), king, + צֶדֶק (tzedek), righteousness. Melchizedek = king of righteousness. Priest-king of Salem (Gen 14:18). Hitchcock: king of justice. BehindTheName: From Hebrew מַלְכִּי־צֶדֶק meaning 'my king is righteousness'.
H4442.significance: Without genealogy (Heb 7:3); blesses Abraham, receives tithes. Type of Christ as priest forever after the order of Melchizedek (Ps 110:4; Heb 7).

H3130.meaning: From יָסַף (yasaf), add, increase. Joseph = may he add. Son of Jacob; sold into Egypt (Gen 37:28). Hitchcock: increase; addition. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יוֹסֵף (Yosef) meaning 'he will add', from יָסַף (yasaf) 'to add'.
H3130.significance: Type of Christ in suffering and exaltation (Gen 37–50). Rejected by brothers, exalted to the right hand of Pharaoh; saves the nations. “God has made me forget” (Gen 41:51)—sorrow turned to fruitfulness.

H7354.meaning: From רָחֵל (rachel), ewe. Rachel = ewe. Wife of Jacob; mother of Joseph and Benjamin (Gen 29–35). Hitchcock: sheep. BehindTheName: From Hebrew רָחֵל (Raḥel) meaning 'ewe'.
H7354.significance: Beloved of Jacob; wept for children (Jer 31:15; Matt 2:18). Her tomb marks the way; her sons become the chief tribes. Type of the bride and of maternal grief.

H5146.meaning: From נוֹחַ (Noach), rest. Noah = rest. Son of Lamech; preserved through the flood (Gen 6–9). Hitchcock: repose; consolation | that quavers or totters (Zelophehad's daughter). BehindTheName: From Hebrew נֹחַ (Noaḥ) meaning 'rest, comfort'.
H5146.significance: Preacher of righteousness (2 Pet 2:5); type of salvation and new creation. The ark as type of Christ—refuge from judgment. Covenant of the bow (Gen 9:13).

H8035.meaning: From שֵׁם (shem), name. Shem = name. Son of Noah (Gen 5:32); brother of Ham and Japheth. Hitchcock: name; renown. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שֵׁם (Shem) meaning 'name'.
H8035.significance: Line of the covenant (Gen 9:26–27); blessed of the Lord. Father of the Semitic peoples; in his line comes Abraham and the promise.

H3389.meaning: Hebrew יְרוּשָׁלַ͏ִם (Yerushalayim); possibly foundation of peace or teaching of peace. Capital of Judah; city of the great King. Hitchcock: vision of peace
H3389.significance: City of David; site of the temple. Where the Lord chose to put his name (Deut 12:11). Type of the heavenly Jerusalem (Heb 12:22; Rev 21:2).

H0894.meaning: From בָּלַל (balal), confound. Babel/Babylon = confusion (Gen 11:9). Mesopotamian empire; later symbol of worldly power (Rev 17–18). Hitchcock: same as Babel
H0894.significance: Tower of Babel—man’s rebellion and scattering (Gen 11). Worldly kingdom; man’s substitute for God’s rule. Type of the city that opposes the Lamb.

H2332.meaning: From חָוָה (chawah), live, or חַי (chay), life. Eve = life. First woman; mother of all living (Gen 3:20). Hitchcock: living; enlivening. BehindTheName: From Hebrew חַוָּה (Ḥawwa) meaning 'to breathe' or 'living'.
H2332.significance: Taken from Adam; mother of Cain, Abel, Seth. Deceived (1 Tim 2:14) yet given the promise of the seed (Gen 3:15). Type of the church as bride.

H7014.meaning: From קָנָה (qanah), acquire, get. Cain = acquisition. Firstborn of Adam (Gen 4:1). Hitchcock: possession, or possessed. BehindTheName: From Hebrew קָיִן (Qayin) possibly meaning 'acquired', from קָנָה (qana) 'to acquire'.
H7014.significance: Offered unacceptable sacrifice; slew Abel (Gen 4:8). Name (acquire) as grasping—land, offering, brother’s life. Type of the way of the flesh (Jude 11).

H8052.meaning: From שָׁמַע (shama), hear, + אֵל (el), God. Samuel = heard of God, or name of God. Prophet and judge (1 Sam 1:20).
H8052.significance: Asked of the Lord; dedicated before birth. Anoints Saul and David; bridge from judges to kingdom. “Speak, for your servant hears” (1 Sam 3:10).

H0452.meaning: From אֵל (el) + יָהּ (Yah). Elijah = my God is YHWH. Prophet (1 Ki 17:1). Hitchcock: God the Lord, the strong Lord. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אֵלִיָּהוּ (ʾEliyyahu) meaning 'my God is Yahweh'.
H0452.significance: Prophet of fire; confronts Ahab and Baal (1 Ki 18). Type of the forerunner (Mal 4:5; Matt 17:3). Taken up in a whirlwind (2 Ki 2:11); John the Baptist comes in his spirit.

H0477.meaning: From אֵל (el) + יָשַׁע (yasha), save. Elisha = God is salvation. Successor of Elijah (1 Ki 19:16). Hitchcock: salvation of God. BehindTheName: From Hebrew אֱלִישָׁע meaning 'my God is salvation'.
H0477.significance: Asks for double portion (2 Ki 2:9); many signs—healing, provision, resurrection. Name (God saves) fits his ministry. Continuation of Elijah’s mantle.

H1840.meaning: From דָּן (dan), judge, + אֵל (el), God. Daniel = God is my judge. Exile prophet (Dan 1:6). Hitchcock: judgment of God; God my judge. BehindTheName: From Hebrew דָּנִיֵּאל meaning 'God is my judge', from דִּין (din) 'to judge' and אֵל (ʾel) 'God'.
H1840.significance: Interpreter of dreams and visions; faithful in the court of Babylon. Lion’s den (Dan 6); type of the wise one who keeps the law and is vindicated by God.

H0635.meaning: From Persian or Hebrew; possibly “star” (Persian) or “hidden.” Esther = queen in Persia (Est 2:7). Hitchcock: secret; hidden. BehindTheName: Possibly from Persian meaning 'star', or from Ishtar.
H0635.significance: Jewish queen who risked her life for her people (Est 4:16). “For such a time as this.” Type of providence and the hidden hand of God in exile.

H7342.meaning: From רָחַב (rachav), breadth, wide. Rahab = breadth. Canaanite woman of Jericho (Josh 2:1).
H7342.significance: Hid the spies; spared with her household (Josh 6:25). In the line of Christ (Matt 1:5); type of faith and the inclusion of the nations (Heb 11:31; James 2:25).

H7327.meaning: From רֵעַ (rea), friend, companion. Ruth = friend, companion. Moabitess (Ruth 1:4). Hitchcock: drunk; satisfied. BehindTheName: From Hebrew רוּת (Rut) possibly meaning 'friend'.
H7327.significance: Covenant loyalty (ḥesed); “your people shall be my people” (Ruth 1:16). Ancestress of David; type of the Gentile bride and the kinsman-redeemer (Boaz).

G2424.meaning: Greek Ἰησοῦς (Iesous); from Hebrew יְהוֹשֻׁעַ (Yehoshua). Jesus = YHWH saves. Hitchcock: savior; deliverer. BehindTheName: From Greek Ἰησοῦς (Iesous), from Hebrew יֵשׁוּעַ (Yeshuaʿ), short form of יְהוֹשֻׁעַ (Yehoshuaʿ) meaning 'Yahweh is salvation'.
G2424.significance: The name given by the angel (Matt 1:21); the name above every name (Phil 2:9). Covenant salvation in person—God with us. No other name under heaven (Acts 4:12).

G5547.meaning: Greek Χριστός (Christos); from χρίω (chrio), anoint. Christ = anointed one.
G5547.significance: Messiah; King and Priest. The anointed of the Lord; fulfills the offices of prophet, priest, and king. Jesus is the Christ (Matt 16:16).

G3323.meaning: Greek Μεσσίας (Messias); from Hebrew מָשִׁיחַ (mashiach), anointed. Messiah = anointed one.
G3323.significance: Hebrew title for the coming King (John 1:41; 4:25). Jesus is the Messiah—the one anointed to redeem and rule.

G2491.meaning: Greek Ἰωάννης (Ioannes); from Hebrew יוֹחָנָן (Yochanan), Yah is gracious. John = Yah is gracious. Hitchcock: the grace or mercy of the Lord. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יוֹחָנָן (Yoḥanan) meaning 'Yahweh is gracious'.
G2491.significance: Baptist and apostle; forerunner who points to the Lamb (John 1:29). “He must increase, I must decrease.” Name (gracious) fits the one who announces grace.

G3137.meaning: Greek Μαρία (Maria); from Hebrew מִרְיָם (Miriam). Mary = bitterness or rebellion; possibly “beloved.” Mother of Jesus (Luke 1:30). Hitchcock: same as Miriam. BehindTheName: From Greek Μαρία (Maria), from Hebrew מִרְיָם (Miryam), meaning uncertain, possibly 'sea of bitterness' or 'rebelliousness'.
G3137.significance: The Lord’s handmaid (Luke 1:38); virgin mother of the Son. At the cross (John 19:25); name and role—the one who bore the Savior.

G4074.meaning: Greek Πέτρος (Petros); from πέτρα (petra), rock. Peter = rock. Apostle (Matt 16:18). Hitchcock: a rock or stone. BehindTheName: From Greek Πέτρος (Petros) meaning 'stone'.
G4074.significance: Cephas; confessor (“You are the Christ”) and foundation of the church. Denied three times, restored three times (John 21). Name (rock) as the one on whom Christ builds.

G3972.meaning: Greek Παῦλος (Paulos); Latin Paulus = small. Apostle (Acts 13:9). Hitchcock: small; little. BehindTheName: From Latin Paulus meaning 'small, humble'.
G3972.significance: Apostle to the Gentiles; from persecutor to preacher (Acts 9). “Least of the apostles” (1 Cor 15:9)—name (small) fits his self-understanding and the grace given him.

G2384.meaning: Greek Ἰακώβ (Iakob); from Hebrew Jacob. Jacob = supplanter. Hitchcock: that supplants, undermines; the heel. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יַעֲקֹב (Yaʿaqov) possibly meaning 'holder of the heel' or 'supplanter', from עָקַב (ʿaqav) 'heel'.
G2384.significance: Patriarch; father of the twelve tribes. NT references to Israel and the covenant promises (Rom 9:13; Heb 11:21).

G2464.meaning: Greek Ἰσαάκ (Isaak); from Hebrew Isaac. Isaac = he laughs.
G2464.significance: Son of promise; type of Christ as the offered son (Heb 11:17–19). Seed through whom the covenant runs (Gal 4:28).

G1138.meaning: Greek Δαυίδ (David); from Hebrew David. David = beloved.
G1138.significance: King; type of Christ (Acts 2:30; Rom 1:3). Son of David—the promised heir to the throne.

G2501.meaning: Greek Ἰωσήφ (Ioseph); from Hebrew Joseph. Joseph = may he add. Hitchcock: increase; addition. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יוֹסֵף (Yosef) meaning 'he will add', from יָסַף (yasaf) 'to add'.
G2501.significance: Husband of Mary; earthly father of Jesus (Matt 1:16). Righteous man; obeyed the angel (Matt 2:13–14). Name (add) as the one who did not subtract from the law but fulfilled it.

G2385.meaning: Greek Ἰάκωβος (Iakobos); from Hebrew Jacob. James = supplanter. Multiple: son of Zebedee, son of Alphaeus, brother of the Lord. Hitchcock: same as Jacob. BehindTheName: English form of Iacomus (Latin), from Jacob.
G2385.significance: James son of Zebedee: apostle, martyr (Acts 12:2). James brother of the Lord: leader in Jerusalem (Acts 15), author of James. Name in the circle of the Twelve and the family of Jesus.

G2381.meaning: Greek Θωμᾶς (Thomas); Aramaic תְּאוֹמָא (te’oma), twin. Thomas = twin. Hitchcock: a twin. BehindTheName: From Aramaic תְּאוֹמָא (Teʾoma) meaning 'twin'.
G2381.significance: One of the Twelve; “Unless I see…” (John 20:25). Doubting Thomas who confesses “My Lord and my God” (John 20:28). Type of faith that moves from sight to confession.

G0406.meaning: Greek Ἀνδρέας (Andreas); from ἀνήρ (aner), man. Andrew = manly. Apostle (Matt 4:18). Hitchcock: a strong man. BehindTheName: From Greek Ἀνδρέας (Andreas), from ἀνδρεῖος (andreios) 'manly', from ἀνήρ (aner) 'man'.
G0406.significance: Brother of Peter; first called with John (John 1:40). Brought Peter to Jesus. Name (manly) as the one who follows and brings others.

G3156.meaning: Greek Μαθθαῖος (Matthaios); from Hebrew מַתִּתְיָהוּ (Mattityahu), gift of Yah. Matthew = gift of Yah. Apostle; tax collector (Matt 9:9). BehindTheName: From Greek Ματθαῖος (Matthaios), from Hebrew מַתִּתְיָהוּ (Mattityahu) meaning 'gift of Yahweh'.
G3156.significance: Author of the first Gospel; from tax collector to disciple. Name (gift of Yah) as the one given to record the gift of the King.

G3065.meaning: Greek Λουκᾶς (Loukas); from Latin Lucius. Luke = light. Physician; companion of Paul (Col 4:14). Hitchcock: luminous; white. BehindTheName: From Greek Λουκᾶς (Loukas), from Latin Lucius 'light'.
G3065.significance: Author of Luke and Acts; historian of the gospel and the church. “Orderly account” (Luke 1:3); name (light) as the one who brings the light of the narrative.

G2883.meaning: Greek Κορνήλιος (Kornelios); from Latin Cornelius. Cornelius = of a horn. Centurion (Acts 10:1). BehindTheName: Roman name possibly from Latin cornu 'horn'.
G2883.significance: God-fearer; first Gentile to receive the Spirit in Acts (Acts 10:44–48). Type of the opening of the gospel to the nations; name (horn) as strength and salvation (Ps 18:2).

G0912.meaning: From בַּר (bar), son, + אַבָּא (abba), father. Barabbas = son of the father. Prisoner released at Passover (Matt 27:16). Hitchcock: son of shame, confusion
G0912.significance: Insurrectionist and murderer; chosen by the crowd over Jesus (Matt 27:21). Type of the guilty one released while the innocent is condemned—substitution.

G2264.meaning: Greek Ἡρῴδης (Herodes); from Greek hero. Herod = heroic. Dynasty of Idumean kings (Matt 2; Luke 23; Acts 12). Hitchcock: son of a hero
G2264.significance: Herod the Great: slew infants (Matt 2:16). Herod Antipas: beheaded John (Mark 6). Herod Agrippa: persecuted the church (Acts 12). Name (heroic) vs. tyranny—the world’s “hero” against the true King.

G0452.meaning: Greek Ἅννας (Hannas); from Hebrew חָנַן (chanan), gracious. Annas = gracious. High priest (Luke 3:2; John 18:13). Hitchcock: one who answers; humble. BehindTheName: Contracted form of Ananias.
G0452.significance: Former high priest; father-in-law of Caiaphas. Jesus brought before him (John 18:13). Name (gracious) vs. role in the condemnation of the righteous.

G0367.meaning: Greek Ἁνανίας (Ananias); from Hebrew חָנַן (chanan), gracious. Ananias = Yah is gracious. Multiple: disciple in Damascus (Acts 9:10), husband of Sapphira (Acts 5:1). Hitchcock: or Ananiah, the cloud of the Lord. BehindTheName: Greek form of Hananiah.
G0367.significance: Ananias of Damascus: obeyed the Lord and baptized Paul (Acts 9:17). Ananias and Sapphira: lied to the Spirit and fell (Acts 5:5). Same name, opposite fates.

G0625.meaning: Greek Ἀπολλῶς (Apollos); possibly from Apollo. Apollos = from Apollo. Alexandrian Jew (Acts 18:24). Hitchcock: one who destroys; destroyer
G0625.significance: Eloquent; knew only John’s baptism; instructed by Priscilla and Aquila (Acts 18:26). Fellow worker with Paul (1 Cor 3:6). Name in the service of the word.

G0207.meaning: Latin Aquila = eagle. Husband of Priscilla; tentmaker (Acts 18:2). Hitchcock: an eagle. BehindTheName: Latin meaning 'eagle'.
G0207.significance: With Priscilla, instructed Apollos (Acts 18:26); greeted by Paul (Rom 16:3). Name (eagle) as one who soars in the word; partner in ministry.

G1050.meaning: Latin Gaius. Gaius = rejoice. Multiple in NT: host (Rom 16:23), Macedonian (Acts 19:29), recipient of 3 John. Hitchcock: lord; an earthly man
G1050.significance: Paul’s host (“host of the whole church” Rom 16:23); one of the few who supported the apostle. Name (rejoice) in the fellowship of the gospel.

G1059.meaning: Greek Γαμαλιήλ (Gamaliel); from Hebrew גְּמַלִּיאֵל (Gamaliel), reward of God. Gamaliel = reward of God. Pharisee; teacher of Paul (Acts 5:34; 22:3). Hitchcock: recompense of God; camel of God
G1059.significance: Counseled tolerance toward the apostles (Acts 5:34–39); “if it is of God, you cannot overthrow it.” Name (reward of God) as the teacher under whom Paul learned the law.

G1115.meaning: Greek Γολγοθᾶ (Golgotha); from Aramaic גּוּלְגֹּלְתָא (gulgolta), skull. Golgotha = place of the skull. Hitchcock: a heap of skulls; something skull-shaped
G1115.significance: Place of crucifixion (Matt 27:33; John 19:17). Name (skull) as the place of death—and of the death that brings life. Calvary (Latin calvaria = skull).

G1068.meaning: Hebrew גַּת־שְׁמָנִים (Gat Shemanim); oil press. Gethsemane = oil press. Garden on the Mount of Olives (Matt 26:36). Hitchcock: a very fat or plentiful vale
G1068.significance: Where Jesus prayed before the arrest; “let this cup pass” (Matt 26:39). Name (oil press) as the place of crushing—the Son pressed in agony, yielding the oil of obedience.

G0963.meaning: Hebrew בֵּית עֲנִיָּה (Beth Aniyah); house of affliction or poor. Bethany = house of the poor/affliction. Village near Jerusalem (Matt 21:17). Hitchcock: the house of song; the house of affliction
G0963.significance: Home of Mary, Martha, Lazarus; where Jesus was anointed (John 12:3); from here he ascended (Luke 24:50). Name (house of affliction) as the place of friendship and anointing before the cross.

G2584.meaning: Hebrew כְּפַר נַחוּם (Kfar Nachum); village of Nahum. Capernaum = village of consolation. Town on the Sea of Galilee (Matt 4:13). Hitchcock: the field of repentance; city of comfort
G2584.significance: Jesus’ base in Galilee; many miracles and teachings there. “Exalted to heaven” but brought down (Matt 11:23). Name (consolation) as the place that received the Consoler—and would be judged for unbelief.

G2181.meaning: Greek Ἔφεσος (Ephesos); possibly “permitted.” Ephesus = major city of Asia Minor (Acts 19:1). Hitchcock: desirable
G2181.significance: Paul’s long ministry there (Acts 19); one of the seven churches (Rev 2:1). Temple of Artemis; riot (Acts 19:23). Name in the spread of the gospel and the call to repent (Rev 2:5).

G2882.meaning: Greek Κόρινθος (Korinthos). Corinth = city on the isthmus; commercial and cosmopolitan. Hitchcock: which is satisfied; ornament; beauty
G2882.significance: Paul founded the church (Acts 18); wrote 1–2 Corinthians. Faction and immorality; “sanctified in Christ” (1 Cor 1:2) yet in need of correction. Name as the church in the world.

G2332.meaning: Greek Θεσσαλονίκη (Thessalonike); victory over Thessaly. Thessalonica = city in Macedonia. Hitchcock: victory against the Thessalians
G2332.significance: Paul preached there (Acts 17:1); received the letters 1–2 Thessalonians. Church of the Thessalonians in God (1 Thess 1:1); name in the apostolic mission.

G0490.meaning: Greek Ἀντιόχεια (Antiocheia); from Antiochus. Antioch = city in Syria (Acts 11:26). Hitchcock: speedy as a chariot
G0490.significance: Where disciples were first called Christians (Acts 11:26). Base for Paul’s missions (Acts 13:1). Name as the birthplace of the name “Christian.”

G0828.meaning: Latin Augustus = revered, majestic. Title of Caesar (Luke 2:1). Hitchcock: increased, augmented
G0828.significance: Decree that brought Mary and Joseph to Bethlehem (Luke 2:1)—unwitting servant of the prophecy (Mic 5:2). Name (majestic) as the world’s ruler whose decree fulfills the true King’s birth.

G2958.meaning: Latin Quirinius. Quirinius = governor of Syria (Luke 2:2).
G2958.significance: Registration under his governorship dates the birth of Jesus (Luke 2:2). Name in the intersection of imperial power and the nativity.

G2321.meaning: Greek Θεόφιλος (Theophilus); from θεός (theos), God, + φίλος (philos), friend. Theophilus = friend of God, or loved by God.
G2321.significance: Addressee of Luke and Acts (Luke 1:3; Acts 1:1). Name (loved by God) as the one for whom the orderly account is written—and every reader who seeks certainty.

G3127.meaning: Greek Μαναήν (Manaen); from Hebrew מְנַחֵם (Menachem), comforter. Manaen = comforter. Foster brother of Herod the tetrarch (Acts 13:1). Hitchcock: a comforter; a leader
G3127.significance: Prophet or teacher in Antioch (Acts 13:1); in the circle that sent Paul and Barnabas. Name (comforter) in the ministry of the word.

G2216.meaning: Hebrew זְרֻבָּבֶל (Zerubbabel); from זֶרַע (zera), seed, + בָּבֶל (Babel). Zerubbabel = seed of Babylon. Governor of Judah (Ezra 2:2; Hag 1:1). Hitchcock: a stranger at Babylon; dispersion of confusion. BehindTheName: From Hebrew זְרֻבָּבֶל possibly meaning 'seed of Babylon'.
G2216.significance: Led the return; laid the foundation of the second temple (Ezra 3:8). In the line of David (Matt 1:12); name (seed of Babylon) as the one who came out of exile to rebuild.

G2199.meaning: Greek Ζεβεδαῖος (Zebedaios); from Hebrew זְבַדְיָה (Zevadyah), Yah has given. Zebedee = Yah has given. Father of James and John (Matt 4:21). Hitchcock: abundant; portion
G2199.significance: Fisherman; sons left him to follow Jesus (Matt 4:22). Name (Yah has given) as the one whose sons were given to the gospel—and asked for the right and left hand (Matt 20:21).

G3070.meaning: Greek Λυδία (Lydia); from region Lydia. Lydia = woman of Lydia. Seller of purple (Acts 16:14). BehindTheName: From Greek Λυδία, referring to the region.
G3070.significance: First European convert (Acts 16:14); “Lord opened her heart.” Hostess at Philippi. Name (from Lydia) as the one through whom the gospel entered Europe.

G3136.meaning: Greek Μάρθα (Martha); Aramaic מַרְתָּא (Marta), lady, mistress. Martha = lady. Hitchcock: who becomes bitter; provoking. BehindTheName: From Aramaic מַרְתָּא (Marta) meaning 'the lady, the mistress'.
G3136.significance: Sister of Mary and Lazarus; “anxious and troubled about many things” (Luke 10:41). Served; confessed “You are the Christ” (John 11:27). Name (lady) as the one who served—and was called to the one thing needful.

G3138.meaning: Greek Μάρκος (Markos); Latin Marcus. Mark = from Mars, or hammer. John Mark (Acts 12:12). Hitchcock: same as Marcus. BehindTheName: From Latin Marcus, possibly from Mars.
G3138.significance: Companion of Paul and Peter; author of the second Gospel. Deserted (Acts 15:38) but later useful (2 Tim 4:11). Name in the writing of the gospel of the suffering Son.

G2455.meaning: Greek Ἰούδας (Ioudas); from Hebrew Judah. Jude = praise. Author of the letter of Jude (Jude 1).
G2455.significance: Servant of Jesus Christ, brother of James (Jude 1:1). Contends for the faith (Jude 3). Name (praise) as the one who calls the church to persevere.

G1214.meaning: Greek Δημᾶς (Demas); possibly short for Demetrius. Demas = companion of Paul (Col 4:14). Hitchcock: popular
G1214.significance: Once with Paul (Phlm 24); later “in love with this present world” (2 Tim 4:10). Name as the one who turned away—warning against apostasy.

G0708.meaning: Greek Ἀρίσταρχος (Aristarchos); from ἄριστος (aristos), best, + ἀρχή (arche), ruler. Aristarchus = best ruler. Macedonian (Acts 19:29). Hitchcock: the best prince
G0708.significance: Traveled with Paul (Acts 20:4); with him in the riot at Ephesus and on the voyage to Rome. “Fellow prisoner” (Col 4:10). Name (best ruler) as the one who served the apostle.

G2037.meaning: Greek Ἔραστος (Erastus); from ἐραστός (erastos), beloved. Erastus = beloved. City treasurer (Rom 16:23). Hitchcock: lovely, amiable
G2037.significance: One of Paul’s helpers (Acts 19:22); “city treasurer” in Corinth (Rom 16:23). Name (beloved) in the list of those who served the church.

G2921.meaning: Greek Κρίσπος (Krispos); from Latin Crispus. Crispus = curled. Ruler of the synagogue (Acts 18:8).
G2921.significance: Believed with his household (Acts 18:8); Paul baptized him (1 Cor 1:14). Name (curled) as the one who turned from synagogue to Christ.

G2383.meaning: Greek Ἰάειρος (Iaeiros); from Hebrew יָאִיר (Yair), he will enlighten. Jairus = he will enlighten. Ruler of the synagogue (Mark 5:22). BehindTheName: From Hebrew יָאִיר meaning 'he shines'.
G2383.significance: Begged Jesus to heal his daughter (Mark 5:23); daughter raised (Mark 5:42). Name (he will enlighten) as the one whose house was enlightened by the resurrection.

G3124.meaning: Greek Μάλχος (Malchos); from Hebrew מֶלֶךְ (melek), king. Malchus = king. Servant of the high priest (John 18:10). Hitchcock: my king, kingdom, or counselor
G3124.significance: Ear cut off by Peter; healed by Jesus (Luke 22:51). Name (king) as the servant of the high priest—and the one who received mercy from the true King.

G2582.meaning: Greek Κανδάκη (Kandake); title of Ethiopian queen. Candace = queen of the Ethiopians (Acts 8:27). Hitchcock: who possesses contrition. BehindTheName: From Cushitic kdke meaning 'queen mother'.
G2582.significance: Her eunuch was reading Isaiah and was baptized by Philip (Acts 8:27–38). Name (title) as the power from whose court the gospel reached the ends (Acts 1:8).

G0959.meaning: Greek Βερνίκη (Bernike); from Greek, bringer of victory. Bernice = bringer of victory. Sister of Agrippa II (Acts 25:13). Hitchcock: one that brings victory
G0959.significance: Present with Agrippa when Paul made his defense (Acts 25:23). Name (victory) as the one who heard the gospel in the royal court—and did not believe.

G1409.meaning: Greek Δρούσιλλα (Drousilla); from Latin Drusilla. Drusilla = wife of Felix (Acts 24:24). Hitchcock: watered by the dew
G1409.significance: Jewish wife of the Roman governor; with Felix heard Paul speak of righteousness and judgment (Acts 24:25). Felix was afraid—but did not repent.

G0986.meaning: Greek Βλάστος (Blastos); from βλαστός (blastos), bud. Blastus = chamberlain of Herod (Acts 12:20). Hitchcock: that buds or brings forth
G0986.significance: Mediated between Tyre and Sidon and Herod (Acts 12:20). Name (bud) as the one in the court when Herod was struck (Acts 12:23)—the king’s servant and the King’s judgment.

G0249.meaning: Greek Ἐλισάβετ (Elisabet); from Hebrew אֱלִישֶׁבַע (Elisheva), my God is oath. Elizabeth = my God is oath. Mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:5).
G0249.significance: Wife of Zechariah; relative of Mary; “blessed is she who believed” (Luke 1:45). Name (God is oath) as the one who bore the forerunner—the oath fulfilled.

G2197.meaning: Greek Ζαχαρίας (Zacharias); from Hebrew זְכַרְיָה (Zechariah), Yah has remembered. Zechariah = Yah has remembered. Father of John the Baptist (Luke 1:5). Hitchcock: same as Zachariah. BehindTheName: From Hebrew זְכַרְיָה meaning 'Yahweh remembers'.
G2197.significance: Priest; struck mute until John’s birth (Luke 1:20, 64). Sang the Benedictus (Luke 1:68–79). Name (Yah has remembered) as the one who announced the dawn from on high.

G2489.meaning: Greek Ἰωάννα (Ioanna); from Hebrew יוֹחָנָן (Yochanan). Joanna = Yah is gracious. Wife of Chuza (Luke 8:3). Hitchcock: grace or gift of the Lord
G2489.significance: Among the women who supported Jesus and the Twelve (Luke 8:3); at the empty tomb (Luke 24:10). Name (gracious) as the one who received and proclaimed grace.

G2131.meaning: Greek Εὐνίκη (Eunike); from εὐ (eu), good, + νίκη (nike), victory. Eunice = good victory. Mother of Timothy (2 Tim 1:5).
G2131.significance: Jewish mother; faith that dwelt in her and in Lois (2 Tim 1:5). Name (good victory) as the one who passed the faith to Timothy.

G3090.meaning: Greek Λωΐς (Lois); possibly from λωΐον (loion), better. Lois = grandmother of Timothy (2 Tim 1:5).
G3090.significance: Faith that dwelt in Lois and Eunice (2 Tim 1:5). Name in the line of faith—grandmother to Timothy, servant of the gospel.

G0451.meaning: Greek Ἄννα (Anna); from Hebrew חַנָּה (Hannah), grace. Anna = grace. Prophetess (Luke 2:36). Hitchcock: gracious; one who gives. BehindTheName: Greek form of Hannah.
G0451.significance: Widow; in the temple when Jesus was presented (Luke 2:36–38). Spoke of him to all who were waiting. Name (grace) as the one who recognized the redemption of Jerusalem.

G3003.meaning: Latin Legio. Legion = Roman military unit; name of the demons in the Gerasene (Mark 5:9).
G3003.significance: “My name is Legion; for we are many” (Mark 5:9). The multitude of evil; cast into the pigs. Name as the confession of the unclean spirit before the Son of God.

G2394.meaning: Greek Ἰάσων (Iason); from Greek ἰάομαι (iaomai), heal. Jason = healer. Host of Paul in Thessalonica (Acts 17:5). Hitchcock: he that cures. BehindTheName: From Greek Ἰάσων possibly meaning 'healer'.
G2394.significance: Paul and Silas stayed with him (Acts 17:7); dragged before the authorities (Acts 17:6). Name (healer) as the one who received the apostles—and bore the cost.

G0711.meaning: Greek Ἀριστόβουλος (Aristoboulos); from ἄριστος (aristos), best, + βουλή (boule), counsel. Aristobulus = best counsel. In Rome (Rom 16:10). Hitchcock: a good counselor. BehindTheName: From Greek meaning 'best in counsel', from ἄριστος (aristos) 'best' and βουλή (boule) 'counsel'.
G0711.significance: Household greeted by Paul (Rom 16:10). Name (best counsel) in the list of the saints in the capital.

H7586.meaning: From שָׁאַל (shaal), ask. Saul = asked (of God). First king of Israel (1 Sam 9:2). Hitchcock: demanded; lent; ditch; death. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שָׁאוּל (Shaʾul) meaning 'asked for, prayed for'.
H7586.significance: Asked for by the people (1 Sam 8:5); rejected by the Lord (1 Sam 15:26). Name (asked) as the one given and then taken away—type of the king who did not obey.

H3083.meaning: From יָהּ (Yah) + נָתַן (natan), give. Jonathan = Yah has given. Son of Saul (1 Sam 14:1). Hitchcock: given of God. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יוֹנָתָן (Yonatan) meaning 'Yahweh has given'.
H3083.significance: Friend of David; covenant with him (1 Sam 18:3). Died with Saul at Gilboa (1 Sam 31:2). Name (Yah has given) as the gift of friendship—and the one who yielded the kingdom to David.

H3414.meaning: From רָם (ram), exalt, + יָהּ (Yah). Jeremiah = Yah exalts, or Yah loosens (womb). Prophet (Jer 1:1). Hitchcock: exaltation of the Lord. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יִרְמְיָהוּ meaning 'Yahweh will exalt'.
H3414.significance: Prophet of the fall of Jerusalem; weeping prophet (Jer 9:1). Name (Yah exalts) as the one who spoke the word of judgment—and of the new covenant (Jer 31:31).

H3168.meaning: From חָזַק (chazaq), strengthen, + אֵל (el), God. Ezekiel = God strengthens. Exile prophet (Ezek 1:3). Hitchcock: the strength of God. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יְחֶזְקֵאל meaning 'God strengthens'.
H3168.significance: Prophet of the glory and the dry bones (Ezek 37); watchman (Ezek 33:7). Name (God strengthens) as the one who spoke hope in exile.

H3124.meaning: From יוֹנָה (yonah), dove. Jonah = dove. Prophet (Jon 1:1). Hitchcock: or Jonas, a dove; he that oppresses; destroyer. BehindTheName: From Hebrew יוֹנָה (Yona) meaning 'dove'.
H3124.significance: Sent to Nineveh; fled, swallowed, delivered (Jon 1–2). Name (dove) as the one who bore the word—and was cast out and restored. Type of death and resurrection (Matt 12:40).

H4318.meaning: From מִי (mi), who, + כָּמוֹ (kamo), like. Micah = who is like (Yah). Prophet (Mic 1:1). Hitchcock: poor; humble. BehindTheName: From Hebrew מִיכָה (Mikha), short form of Micaiah, meaning 'who is like Yahweh?'.
H4318.significance: Prophet of Bethlehem (Mic 5:2); “who is like God?” (Mic 7:18). Name as the question that points to the one from Bethlehem.

H1035.meaning: Hebrew בֵּית לֶחֶם (Beth Lechem); house of bread. Bethlehem = house of bread. Town in Judah (Ruth 1:1; Matt 2:1).
H1035.significance: City of David; birthplace of Jesus (Matt 2:1; Luke 2:4). Mic 5:2: “from you shall come a ruler.” Name (house of bread) as the place of the Bread of Life.

G3478.meaning: Hebrew נָצְרַת (Natzrat); from נֵצֶר (netzer), branch, or place name. Nazareth = branch town. Town in Galilee (Matt 2:23). Hitchcock: separated; crowned; sanctified
G3478.significance: Where Jesus grew up (Luke 2:51); “can anything good come from Nazareth?” (John 1:46). Name (branch) as the place of the Branch (Isa 11:1)—the shoot from the stump.

G5376.meaning: Greek Φίλιππος (Philippos); from φίλος (philos), friend, + ἵππος (hippos), horse. Philip = lover of horses. Apostle (Matt 10:3); also the evangelist (Acts 8:5). Hitchcock: warlike; a lover of horses. BehindTheName: From Greek Φίλιππος meaning 'friend of horses'.
G5376.significance: Apostle; brought Nathanael to Jesus (John 1:43). Evangelist: baptized the Ethiopian (Acts 8:38). Name (lover of horses) as the one who ran to bring others to the King.

G4736.meaning: Greek Στέφανος (Stephanos); from στέφανος (stephanos), crown. Stephen = crown. Deacon (Acts 6:5). Hitchcock: same as Stephanas. BehindTheName: From Greek Στέφανος (Stephanos) meaning 'crown'.
G4736.significance: First martyr (Acts 7:59); “full of the Spirit” (Acts 6:5). Saw the Son of Man standing (Acts 7:56). Name (crown) as the one who received the crown of life (James 1:12).

G4609.meaning: Greek Σιλᾶς (Silas); from Latin Silvanus. Silas = forest. Companion of Paul (Acts 15:40). Hitchcock: three, or the third. BehindTheName: Probably from Aramaic, related to Saul.
G4609.significance: Prophet; sent with Paul and Barnabas (Acts 15:32). With Paul in prison at Philippi (Acts 16:25); sang and the doors opened. Name in the spread of the gospel.

H8352.meaning: From שִׁית (shit), set, appoint. Seth = appointed, substitute. Third son of Adam (Gen 4:25). Hitchcock: put; who puts; fixed. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שֵׁת (Shet) meaning 'placed, appointed'.
H8352.significance: Given in place of Abel (Gen 4:25); line of the promise (Gen 5:3). Name (appointed) as the seed appointed to carry the hope—type of the line that leads to the Seed.

H7259.meaning: From רָבַק (ravaq), tie, bind. Rebekah = binding, noose. Wife of Isaac (Gen 24:15). Hitchcock: fat; fattened; a quarrel appeased. BehindTheName: From Hebrew רִבְקָה (Rivqa) possibly meaning 'to tie, to bind'.
H7259.significance: Chosen at the well (Gen 24:14); mother of Jacob and Esau. “Two nations in your womb” (Gen 25:23). Name (binding) as the one who bound the covenant to the chosen son.

H3812.meaning: From לָאָה (laah), weary. Leah = weary. Wife of Jacob (Gen 29:16). Hitchcock: weary; tired. BehindTheName: From Hebrew לֵאָה (Leʾa) possibly meaning 'weary'.
H3812.significance: Unloved yet mother of six tribes (Gen 29:31); “Yah has seen my affliction” (Gen 29:32). Name (weary) as the one who bore the burden—and bore Judah, the line of the King.

H1683.meaning: From דְּבוֹרָה (devorah), bee. Deborah = bee. Prophetess and judge (Judg 4:4). Hitchcock: word; thing; a bee. BehindTheName: Means 'bee' in Hebrew.
H1683.significance: Judged Israel; went with Barak to battle (Judg 4:9). “Mother in Israel” (Judg 5:7). Name (bee) as the one who brought the sting of judgment and the honey of deliverance.

H1439.meaning: From גָּדַע (gada), cut off. Gideon = hewer, cutter. Judge (Judg 6:11). Hitchcock: he that bruises or breaks; a destroyer. BehindTheName: From Hebrew גִּדְעוֹן meaning 'feller, hewer'.
H1439.significance: Least in Manasseh (Judg 6:15); “the Lord is peace” (Judg 6:24). Fleece (Judg 6:36–40); 300 (Judg 7:7). Name (cutter) as the one who cut down the altar of Baal—and cut the army to 300.

H8123.meaning: From שֶׁמֶשׁ (shemesh), sun. Samson = sun man, or of the sun. Judge (Judg 13:24). Hitchcock: his sun; his service; there the second time. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שִׁמְשׁוֹן (Shimshon) possibly meaning 'sun', from שֶׁמֶשׁ (shemesh).
H8123.significance: Nazirite; strength in his hair (Judg 16:17). Betrayed by Delilah; died with the Philistines (Judg 16:30). Name (sun) as the one whose strength was the Lord’s—and whose fall was his own.

H4782.meaning: From מָרְדֳּכַי (Mordechai); possibly from Marduk (Babylonian god) or Hebrew “little man.” Mordecai = cousin of Esther (Est 2:5). Hitchcock: contrition; bitter; bruising. BehindTheName: From Hebrew מָרְדֳּכַי possibly from Akkadian Marduk.
H4782.significance: Refused to bow to Haman (Est 3:2); “for such a time as this” (Est 4:14). Exalted under Xerxes (Est 8:2). Name in the deliverance of the Jews in Persia.

H5281.meaning: From נֹעַם (noam), pleasantness. Naomi = my pleasantness. Mother-in-law of Ruth (Ruth 1:2). Hitchcock: beautiful; agreeable. BehindTheName: From Hebrew נָעֳמִי (Noʿomi) meaning 'pleasantness'.
H5281.significance: “Call me Mara [bitter], for the Almighty has dealt bitterly with me” (Ruth 1:20). Returned with Ruth; Boaz became kinsman-redeemer. Name (pleasant) vs. grief—yet redemption at the end.

H1162.meaning: From בֹּעַז (Boaz); possibly “in him is strength.” Boaz = kinsman (Ruth 2:1). Hitchcock: or Booz, in strength. BehindTheName: Means 'swiftness' in Hebrew.
H1162.significance: Redeemed Ruth and the land (Ruth 4:9–10); in the line of David (Ruth 4:21–22). Type of the kinsman-redeemer—strength in him to redeem. Name in the line of Christ.

G4826.meaning: Greek Συμεών (Simeon); from Hebrew שִׁמְעוֹן (Shimon), heard. Simeon = heard. Righteous man in the temple (Luke 2:25). Hitchcock: that hears or obeys; that is heard. BehindTheName: From Hebrew שִׁמְעוֹן (Shimʿon) meaning 'he has heard'.
G4826.significance: Took the infant Jesus in his arms (Luke 2:28); “now you are letting your servant depart in peace” (Luke 2:29). Name (heard) as the one who heard the promise—and saw the Consolation.

H3878.meaning: From לָוָה (lavah), join, attach. Levi = joined. Third son of Jacob (Gen 29:34). Hitchcock: associated with him. BehindTheName: From Hebrew לֵוִי (Levi) possibly meaning 'joined, attached'.
H3878.significance: Tribe of the priesthood; “now my husband will be joined to me” (Gen 29:34). Scattered in Israel (Gen 49:7); yet the Levites are joined to the Lord (Num 18:2).

H1144.meaning: From בֶּן (ben), son, + יָמִין (yamin), right hand. Benjamin = son of the right hand. Youngest son of Jacob (Gen 35:18). BehindTheName: From Hebrew בִּנְיָמִין meaning 'son of the south' or 'son of the right hand', from בֵּן (ben) 'son' and יָמִין (yamin) 'right hand, south'.
H1144.significance: Born to Rachel in death (Gen 35:18); “son of my sorrow” / “son of the right hand.” Tribe of Saul and Paul. Name (right hand) as the beloved of the father.

G3530.meaning: Greek Νικόδημος (Nikodemos); from νίκη (nike), victory, + δῆμος (demos), people. Nicodemus = victory of the people. Pharisee (John 3:1). BehindTheName: From Greek Νικόδημος meaning 'victory of the people'.
G3530.significance: Came by night (John 3:2); “how can a man be born again?” (John 3:4). Brought myrrh and aloes for Jesus’ burial (John 19:39). Name (victory of the people) as the one who came to the true Victory.

G4091.meaning: Latin Pilatus; from pilum, javelin. Pilate = armed. Governor of Judea (Matt 27:2). Hitchcock: armed with a dart
G4091.significance: Asked “What is truth?” (John 18:38); washed his hands (Matt 27:24). Delivered Jesus to be crucified. Name (armed) as the one with power—who could not see the truth.

H4714.meaning: Hebrew מִצְרַיִם (Mitzrayim); dual of מָצוֹר (matzor), siege. Egypt = the two straits (or land of bondage). Hitchcock: that troubles or oppresses; anguish
H4714.significance: House of slavery (Ex 20:2); place of sojourn and exodus. “Out of Egypt I called my son” (Hos 11:1; Matt 2:15). Type of the world and of deliverance.

H5514.meaning: Hebrew סִינַי (Sinai); from סְנֶה (seneh), thorn bush. Sinai = mountain of the thorn bush. Mountain of the law (Ex 19:1). Hitchcock: a bush; enmity
H5514.significance: Where the Lord gave the law (Ex 20); where Moses saw the glory. “The law was given through Moses” (John 1:17). Name as the place of covenant and theophany.

H5986.meaning: From עָמַס (amas), load, carry. Amos = burden. Prophet (Amos 1:1). Hitchcock: loading; weighty. BehindTheName: From Hebrew עָמַס (ʿamas) meaning 'load, burden'.
H5986.significance: Shepherd of Tekoa (Amos 1:1); “the Lord roars from Zion” (Amos 1:2). Name (burden) as the one who bore the burden of the word—judgment and the hope of the booth (Amos 9:11).

H1954.meaning: From יָשַׁע (yasha), save. Hosea = salvation. Prophet (Hos 1:1). Hitchcock: Hoshea, savior; safety. BehindTheName: From Hebrew הוֹשֵׁעַ meaning 'salvation'.
H1954.significance: Married Gomer as a sign (Hos 1:2); “name him Lo-ammi [not my people]” (Hos 1:9). Yet “in the place where it was said Not my people, it shall be said Sons of the living God” (Hos 1:10; Rom 9:26). Name (salvation) as the prophet of the covenant and the bride.

H5662.meaning: From עָבַד (avad), serve, + יָהּ (Yah). Obadiah = servant of Yah. Prophet (Obad 1:1). Hitchcock: servant of the Lord. BehindTheName: From Hebrew עֹבַדְיָה meaning 'serving Yahweh'.
H5662.significance: Vision concerning Edom (Obad 1:1); “the day of the Lord is near” (Obad 1:15). Name (servant of Yah) as the one who spoke judgment on the brother who did not serve.

H5151.meaning: From נָחַם (nacham), comfort. Nahum = comfort. Prophet (Nah 1:1). Hitchcock: comforter; penitent
H5151.significance: Vision concerning Nineveh (Nah 1:1); “the Lord is slow to anger” (Nah 1:3). Name (comfort) as the one who spoke comfort to Judah—and judgment to the oppressor.

H2265.meaning: From חָבַק (chavaq), embrace. Habakkuk = embrace. Prophet (Hab 1:1). Hitchcock: he that embraces; a wrestler. BehindTheName: From Hebrew חֲבַקּוּק meaning 'embrace'.
H2265.significance: “Why do you make me see iniquity?” (Hab 1:3); “the righteous shall live by his faith” (Hab 2:4; Rom 1:17). Name (embrace) as the one who clung to the word in the midst of judgment.

H6846.meaning: From צָפַן (tsaphan), hide. Zephaniah = Yah has hidden. Prophet (Zeph 1:1). Hitchcock: the Lord is my secret. BehindTheName: From Hebrew צְפַנְיָה meaning 'Yahweh has hidden'.
H6846.significance: “The day of the Lord is near” (Zeph 1:7); “seek the Lord, all you humble” (Zeph 2:3). Name (Yah has hidden) as the one who spoke of the remnant hidden in the day of wrath.

H2292.meaning: From חָג (chag), feast. Haggai = festive. Prophet (Hag 1:1). Hitchcock: feast; solemnity. BehindTheName: From Hebrew חַגַּי meaning 'festive', from חָג (ḥag) 'festival'.
H2292.significance: “Consider your ways” (Hag 1:5); “the latter glory of this house shall be greater than the former” (Hag 2:9). Name (festive) as the one who called the people to rebuild and to hope.

H2148.meaning: From זָכַר (zachar), remember, + יָהּ (Yah). Zechariah = Yah has remembered. Prophet (Zech 1:1). Hitchcock: same as Zachariah. BehindTheName: From Hebrew זְכַרְיָה meaning 'Yahweh remembers'.
H2148.significance: Visions of the lampstand and the Branch (Zech 3–4); “behold, your king is coming” (Zech 9:9). Name (Yah has remembered) as the prophet of the covenant and the coming King.

H4401.meaning: From מַלְאָכִי (Malachi), my messenger. Malachi = my messenger. Prophet (Mal 1:1). Hitchcock: my messenger; my angel. BehindTheName: From Hebrew מַלְאָכִי meaning 'my messenger'.
H4401.significance: Last of the Twelve; “behold, I send my messenger” (Mal 3:1). “Elijah” before the great day (Mal 4:5). Name (my messenger) as the one who points to the Messenger of the covenant.

G0301.meaning: Greek Ἄμως (Amos); from Hebrew Amos. Amos = burden. Prophet (Luke 3:25). Hitchcock: loading; weighty. BehindTheName: From Hebrew עָמַס (ʿamas) meaning 'load, burden'.
G0301.significance: In the genealogy of Jesus (Luke 3:25). Name (burden) in the line that leads to the one who bore the burden of the world.

G1648.meaning: Greek Ἐλεάζαρ (Eleazar); from Hebrew אֶלְעָזָר (Elazar), God has helped. Eleazar = God has helped. In genealogy (Matt 1:15). Hitchcock: help of God, court of God
G1648.significance: In the line of Jesus (Matt 1:15). Name (God has helped) as the line that leads to the one who is our help.

G0918.meaning: Greek Βαρθολομαῖος (Bartholomaios); from Aramaic bar + Ptolemy. Bartholomew = son of Ptolemy. Apostle (Matt 10:3). Hitchcock: a son that suspends the waters. BehindTheName: From Aramaic meaning 'son of Talmai'.
G0918.significance: One of the Twelve; often identified with Nathanael (John 1:45). Name (son of Ptolemy) in the circle of the apostles.

G0924.meaning: Greek Βαρτιμαῖος (Bartimaios); from Aramaic bar + Timaeus. Bartimaeus = son of Timaeus. Blind beggar (Mark 10:46).
G0924.significance: “Son of David, have mercy on me” (Mark 10:48); received his sight (Mark 10:52). Name (son of Timaeus/honor) as the one who received honor from the Son of David.

G0184.meaning: Aramaic חֲקַל דְּמָא (chaqal dema), field of blood. Akeldama = field of blood (Acts 1:19).

G2266.meaning: Greek Ἡρωδιάς (Herodias); from Herod. Herodias = wife of Herod Antipas (Matt 14:3).
